Species Comments: 1st noticed by unfamiliar, high-pitched honking. Slightly smaller than a nearby Canada Goose, with grey body, neck, and head. White patch at base of bright orange beak. bright orange legs/feet. No eye ring, dark eye. Dark splotches on belly. located at approx 39.745086,-104.946333 (via Google Maps).

Swimming in small pond at 39.704083,-105.085734. Swimming with a group of ~90 Canada Geese. Dull pink bill with the white markings at the base of bill. Noticeably thick neck. Strikingly white rump that sat a bit higher in the water than a CG. Feet/legs orange. Back feathers similar in color to CG. Overall size was slightly larger than the CG it was swimming with. Excellent views.
Checklist Comments: no coots seen today, the normal kingfisher not seen either.

Species Comments: Viewed from less than 10 yards at the edge of the small pond that's connected to the lake, pinkish bill, mottled white behind bill, orange legs/feet. Possibly a domestic goose since out of season here.

Species Comments: Found feeding with a small (~10) flock of Canada geese in this area: https://goo.gl/maps/9qkJE. As we were coming down the hill we accidentally flushed them. There was one snow goose in the bunch. It was similar in size to the Canada geese (who were too large to be cackling geese, and had the flight calls of canada geese as well). Snow goose was very white with black primaries. As the flock was flying away from us onto the water, we were unable to see the goose's bill.    Perhaps a complete coincidence, but the last time we birded Standley Lake North, we found a snow goose with a small group of Canada geese in the same spot (checklist: http://ebird.org/ebird/view/checklist?subID=S16160721). On that occasion, we were able to view the birds on the ground and definitively ID the goose as a snow goose.

Location: Barr Lake SP--Neidrach Nature Trail & Visitor Center area
Species Comments: seen from the eagle-nest viewing boardwalk, in a large group of ~1,000 canada geese. Snow geese also present, making for great comparison views.
